summary: In this context, Methanedithione and 1-Heptene are both mentioned as volatile organic compounds (VOCs) analyzed in the plasma headspace of patients with esophageal adenocarcinoma (EAC). However, there is no direct discussion of their relationship or interaction; they are simply part of a list of VOCs that were significantly reduced in EAC patients compared to controls. Their individual roles or connections in the context of EAC diagnosis are not elaborated upon.
